column1: # Name: Rape at the national level, number of police-recorded offences per 100,000

# Definition: “Rape” means sexual intercourse without valid consent. (UN-CTS M3.4) - In the UN-CTS data, the rape rate is calculated per 100,000 population. Therefore the rates for the female population, being the principal victims, are in practice twice as high as those presented.
# Source: UNODC - United Nations Surveys on Crime Trends and the Operations of Criminal Justice Systems (CTS)
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
